02:35.697 --> 02:37.782
Well,
I suppose the answer's yes.

02:40.326 --> 02:41.995
- I've been in love.

02:44.163 --> 02:46.666
Long time ago, mind you.

02:46.749 --> 02:48.626
This [grunts] here is...

02:48.710 --> 02:50.670
[whirring, clicking]

02:50.753 --> 02:52.714
This is a place without love.

02:52.797 --> 02:55.091
- You are loved by millions.
- [chuckles]

02:55.174 --> 02:56.593
- A national hero.

02:56.676 --> 02:58.428
- Then why...

02:58.511 --> 03:02.557
why do you keep down here
underground then, huh?

03:02.640 --> 03:03.933
- You know why.

03:04.017 --> 03:06.102
- Can't breathe down here.

03:06.185 --> 03:07.520
[breathing heavily]

03:07.604 --> 03:10.982
Fresh air, that's--ha.
Yeah, that's what I need.

03:11.065 --> 03:12.567
I need some fresh air--
[machine whirring]

03:12.650 --> 03:13.943
- What you're breathing
right now--

03:14.027 --> 03:15.361
cleanest air in the world,
actually.

03:15.445 --> 03:17.113
I built the A/C system myself.

03:17.196 --> 03:21.117
- No, you built a cage, Fox.
You built a...a fucking cage.

03:21.200 --> 03:23.620
I'm sick of it,
and fucking sick of you.

03:23.703 --> 03:26.581
- This facility was built for
your comfort and protection.

03:26.664 --> 03:29.125
- I don't need protection.

03:29.208 --> 03:32.170
Oh, I just need
to get out of here.

03:32.253 --> 03:34.339
What the bloody hell
am I doing here anyway?

03:34.422 --> 03:36.299
- Whoa--hold on now.
- No.

03:36.382 --> 03:37.634
- Gully. Gully!

03:37.717 --> 03:39.218
Gully,
tell me where you wanna go

03:39.302 --> 03:40.845
and I'll clear it
with the PM's office

03:40.929 --> 03:42.221
and assemble a travel team.

03:42.305 --> 03:43.848
- I don't need
a fucking travel team.

03:43.932 --> 03:45.892
- It's just protocol.
For everyone's safety.

03:45.975 --> 03:48.102
You know regular folks
can get scared of you.

03:48.186 --> 03:49.938
- Well, fuck 'em then.

03:50.021 --> 03:51.522
Fuck 'em.

03:51.606 --> 03:53.191
- Copy that, but unfortunately,

03:53.274 --> 03:55.610
