04:25.348 --> 04:27.684
Ahh...

04:31.312 --> 04:34.023
[cars honking]

04:34.107 --> 04:37.235
[siren wailing]

04:38.820 --> 04:40.279
- Get out, get out!

04:40.363 --> 04:41.447
[man yelps]

04:47.453 --> 04:50.415
[adventurous music]

04:50.498 --> 04:57.588
♪ ♪

05:32.832 --> 05:35.960
[intriguing notes]

05:39.839 --> 05:41.924
- Martha Kane
for Prime Minister Aziz.

05:43.342 --> 05:44.802
When's he back?

05:47.597 --> 05:48.973
Okay.

05:49.057 --> 05:50.683
Thanks.

05:53.186 --> 05:54.979
[door opens]
- Hello?

05:55.063 --> 05:56.272
Sam?

05:56.355 --> 05:58.524
Mrs. Pennyworth's here.

05:59.275 --> 06:01.527
Hi, Mrs. P.
- Good morning.

06:04.155 --> 06:06.741
- Oh, um, it's nothing.

06:08.201 --> 06:11.204
- Mrs. P!
- Here she is! Shiny button.

06:11.287 --> 06:13.831
- Now, you guys
have a great day, huh?

06:14.707 --> 06:17.001
- We'll meet you
at the park later, okay?

06:18.044 --> 06:20.046
Be good for Mrs. P. Yeah?

06:20.129 --> 06:22.882
- I will.
- All right. Mm.

06:24.300 --> 06:26.052
- You'd better.
- Bye, Mummy, bye, Daddy.

06:26.135 --> 06:27.845
- Careful on the steps,
sweetheart.

06:27.929 --> 06:29.347
- Mrs. P, are we gonna do
something fun?

06:33.768 --> 06:36.687
[soft music]

06:36.771 --> 06:43.861
♪ ♪

06:45.321 --> 06:46.823
- We need to talk.

06:46.906 --> 06:48.991
- What time did you get home
last night?

06:49.075 --> 06:51.077
- It was late.

06:52.829 --> 06:54.664
- I guess you--you what?

06:54.747 --> 06:57.166
You--you ran into a door?

06:57.250 --> 06:58.668
- Yeah.

06:58.751 --> 07:00.670
Something like that.

07:00.753 --> 07:02.421
It's just a bump.

07:03.798 --> 07:06.092
- Some desk job.

07:06.175 --> 07:07.552
- Thomas...

07:09.470 --> 07:11.472
I haven't been honest with you.

07:13.391 --> 07:15.893
And I'm sorry. I really am.

07:15.977 --> 07:17.979
- You're sorry?

07:18.062 --> 07:20.731
For leading
a secret double life?

07:20.815 --> 07:22.650
For risking your life?
For deceiving me?

07:22.733 --> 07:24.986
For betraying our marriage?
- I didn't betray our marriage.

07:25.069 --> 07:27.196
- Yes, you did.

07:27.280 --> 07:28.823
And now what?

07:28.906 --> 07:30.575
How are we supposed
to move forward

07:30.658 --> 07:33.202
if I can't trust you
to tell me the truth?

07:33.286 --> 07:35.163
- Want some truth, Thomas?

07:35.246 --> 07:37.957
Your father is neck-deep
in some serious trouble.

07:39.834 --> 07:42.962
- What are you talking about?

07:44.005 --> 07:46.215
- You already know, don't you?

07:46.299 --> 07:47.758
He told you
what he's doing here.

07:47.842 --> 07:50.011
- And what if he did?
What's your involvement?

07:50.094 --> 07:51.637
- But why would he tell you?

07:51.721 --> 07:53.264
Because he wants your help.

07:53.347 --> 07:56.058
- He didn't want my help.
He wanted yours.

07:56.142 --> 07:58.227
And I told him no.

07:58.311 --> 07:59.562
- You did?

07:59.645 --> 08:02.398
- The point is We're married.

08:02.481 --> 08:04.442
We're supposed
to trust each other.

08:04.525 --> 08:06.527
And listen to us.

08:10.114 --> 08:12.366
- Okay, here's what I know.

08:13.701 --> 08:16.245
Wayne Enterprise and the CIA
are here in London

08:16.329 --> 08:17.705
testing a new drug,

08:17.788 --> 08:19.957
only something's
gone badly wrong.

08:20.041 --> 08:21.375
People are getting killed.

08:21.459 --> 08:23.502
And that's why
your father's here, right?

08:26.047 --> 08:28.883
- Something like that.
- So what's gone wrong?

08:28.966 --> 08:31.677
Thomas.
You might as well tell me.

08:31.761 --> 08:33.346
As soon as Aziz
gets back from Paris,

08:33.429 --> 08:35.556
I'm briefing him on all this.

08:38.851 --> 08:40.770
- The doctor that developed
the drug has gone AWOL.

08:40.853 --> 08:42.230
- Glubb.
- Right.

08:42.313 --> 08:45.483
And my father
wants to find him--that's all.

08:45.566 --> 08:47.401
He's done nothing wrong.

08:48.402 --> 08:51.656
Nothing...criminal,
technically.

08:51.739 --> 08:54.283
- Okay, well,
then he's got nothing to fear.

08:54.367 --> 08:57.745
- Jessica Thistle was shot
and killed last night

08:57.828 --> 08:59.497
after going on a second

08:59.580 --> 09:01.791
blood-splattered
killing spree,

09:01.874 --> 09:05.253
this one at the residence
of the singer Sandra Onslow.

09:05.336 --> 09:08.297
The police haven't released
the names of anyone involved

09:08.381 --> 09:12.260
or how Miss Thistle came to be
at the singer's flat.

09:12.343 --> 09:15.054
Miss Thistle was seen
as an example

09:15.137 --> 09:18.266
of the escalating drug use
and depravity

09:18.349 --> 09:21.435
of today's youth
after she gruesomely

09:21.519 --> 09:24.563
and brutally stabbed her
parents to death,

09:24.647 --> 09:26.732
Sir Arnulf and Lady Annabel,

09:26.816 --> 09:31.279
who are being laid to rest
today in a private ceremony.

09:31.362 --> 09:35.074
And now, the surprising
controversy erupting over

09:35.157 --> 09:37.243
the gold medal winner...
- Result.

09:37.326 --> 09:38.703
Didn't even mention us.

09:38.786 --> 09:40.329
Looks like we're in the clear
for this one.

09:40.413 --> 09:44.041
Bravo, Mr. Aziz, for once.

09:44.125 --> 09:45.334
- Yeah.

09:46.419 --> 09:47.837
- You okay?

09:49.755 --> 09:51.966
- Been a long time
since I've killed a woman.

09:52.049 --> 09:53.926
- Hmm. Never pleasant.

09:54.010 --> 09:55.678
- Feels like
I've done something wrong.

09:55.761 --> 09:57.471
- There's always gonna be
cock-ups.

09:57.555 --> 09:59.348
It's nobody's fault.
- Ah.

09:59.432 --> 10:01.350
It was me
that brought her there.

10:01.434 --> 10:04.228
Poor wee hen didn't even know
what she was doing.

10:04.312 --> 10:06.480
- And you did what
you had to do. Enough said.

10:06.564 --> 10:07.940
- Cheers.

10:11.027 --> 10:12.528
- Says in the paper

10:12.611 --> 10:16.657
she was an evil hippie
drug fiend filled with hatred.

10:18.617 --> 10:20.661
That's not bloody fair, is it?

10:20.745 --> 10:22.580
- Well,
she did stab up several people.

10:22.663 --> 10:23.998
Maybe we misjudged her.

10:24.081 --> 10:26.876
- That was the drugs
that made her do it.

10:26.959 --> 10:29.045
She was a fine young woman.

10:29.128 --> 10:32.048
It's not fair, dragging her
name through the mud like that.

10:32.131 --> 10:34.008
- She's brown bread, Daveboy.
She doesn't mind.

10:34.091 --> 10:36.344
[phone ringing]
- What about her family, eh?

10:36.427 --> 10:37.470
Hearing all that shite?

10:37.553 --> 10:38.971
- Oh, forget about it, mate.

10:39.055 --> 10:40.806
Nobody believes
what they read in the papers.

10:40.890 --> 10:42.183
- Lucius Fox for you.

10:42.266 --> 10:44.518
- Tell him I'm not here.
- I did.

10:44.602 --> 10:47.396
Says he knows you're sitting
in the bar with Daveboy.

10:47.480 --> 10:49.899
- I fucking knew he had cameras
in here somewhere.

10:49.982 --> 10:51.567
Did I not tell you that?

10:51.650 --> 10:53.277
- Have you got cameras in here?

10:53.361 --> 10:55.571
- Of course I do.
Never mind that. It's Gully.

10:55.654 --> 10:56.739
He took off.

10:56.822 --> 10:58.866
- Well, it's a lovely day out.

10:58.949 --> 11:00.576
He's entitled.
- Well, that's all very well.

11:00.659 --> 11:01.911
But what if he goes rogue?

11:01.994 --> 11:03.287
- Well,
he's bound to eventually.

11:03.371 --> 11:04.747
Stands to reason.

11:04.830 --> 11:06.457
- We need your help
to bring him in.

11:06.540 --> 11:08.042
Quickly and quietly.

11:08.125 --> 11:09.710
- Sorry.
Had a bit of a long night.

11:09.794 --> 11:11.712
The only thing I'm doing today
is having a nice kip.

11:11.796 --> 11:13.297
[alarm blaring]
- We know where he is.

11:13.381 --> 11:14.673
You should be home
in a few hours.

11:14.757 --> 11:17.551
Easy money.
- [sighs]

11:17.635 --> 11:20.012
If he's in London or
the home counties, you're on.

11:20.096 --> 11:22.765
- Jackpot's betting shop
in Hackney, okay?

11:22.848 --> 11:24.141
- Yeah.

11:24.225 --> 11:25.810
Gully's gone AWOL.

11:25.893 --> 11:27.103
Gotta fetch him home.

11:27.186 --> 11:28.396
- How is Captain Blighty
our problem?

11:28.479 --> 11:30.272
- He's not. It's just a job.

11:30.356 --> 11:31.982
- What about solving
the Thistle case?

11:32.066 --> 11:33.818
- The Thistle case? Hmm.

11:33.901 --> 11:35.319
You discovered any clues,
Miss Marple?

11:35.403 --> 11:37.613
- Aye, fucking boatloads.
- Yeah, like what?

11:37.697 --> 11:39.907
- Well, all that stuff that
Martha said about the drugs

11:39.990 --> 11:41.617
and the CIA
covering their tracks

11:41.700 --> 11:43.494
by killing the fake nanny...

11:43.577 --> 11:46.288
- By Jove, Holmes. I think
you've cracked the case.

11:46.372 --> 11:47.915
- Oh, fuck off. It's a clue.

11:47.998 --> 11:50.626
- Yeah,
a clue best left to MI5.

11:50.709 --> 11:52.378
I'm not fucking about
with the CIA,

11:52.461 --> 11:54.547
not for half an unpaid invoice.

11:54.630 --> 11:56.465
- And what about justice?

11:56.549 --> 11:57.758
- And you call me soft?

11:57.842 --> 11:59.969
Not for justice neither,
and certainly not

12:00.052 --> 12:02.096
with a good paid
collection job on the go.

12:02.179 --> 12:04.974
- Well...
I'm not up for a job today.

12:05.057 --> 12:06.892
- I wasn't asking you.

12:06.976 --> 12:09.353
Get some sleep.
I'll call you later.

12:14.066 --> 12:15.317
- You--you want another?

12:15.401 --> 12:17.319
- Well, I'm here, aren't I?

12:25.327 --> 12:27.121
- Morning.

12:27.204 --> 12:29.290
Thought you'd be at work.

12:29.373 --> 12:31.333
- I told them I'd be late.

12:32.042 --> 12:35.171
- Thought I'd call
that man you recommended today.

12:35.254 --> 12:38.674
See if he can round up
this missing employee.

12:38.757 --> 12:41.886
Put all this behind us.

12:41.969 --> 12:44.221
- I doubt
Alfred can fix this now.

12:44.305 --> 12:46.348
[liquid pouring]
- Why's that?

12:48.309 --> 12:52.021
- Martha knows about
Operation Lullaby State.

12:52.104 --> 12:53.606
And the CIA.

12:55.149 --> 12:57.026
And you.
She's putting it all together.

12:57.109 --> 12:59.737
- You told her?

12:59.820 --> 13:01.030
- She knew.

13:01.113 --> 13:02.781
She's going
to the prime minster

13:02.865 --> 13:04.033
as soon as he gets back
from Paris.

13:04.116 --> 13:05.284
- Christ.

13:05.367 --> 13:07.661
- Let's get ahead
of this thing, Dad.

13:07.745 --> 13:09.538
Let's go
to the English government

13:09.622 --> 13:11.165
and tell them what we know.
- What?

13:11.248 --> 13:14.210
- They can help you
track down this guy.

13:14.293 --> 13:15.628
The, uh, the doctor.

13:15.711 --> 13:17.171
- You think the English
government is just gonna

13:17.254 --> 13:18.881
turn him over to me
once they have him?

13:18.964 --> 13:20.382
Not a chance.

13:20.466 --> 13:22.968
Has Martha told anyone else
about this?

13:23.052 --> 13:24.053
- I doubt it.

13:24.136 --> 13:26.013
She reports directly to Aziz.

13:26.096 --> 13:28.432
- Well, that's something,
I guess.

13:30.267 --> 13:32.353
- What's going on, Dad?

13:32.436 --> 13:33.729
What are you not telling me?

13:33.812 --> 13:35.397
- Nothing.

13:35.481 --> 13:37.733
- On your mother's grave,
I've told you everything.

13:39.652 --> 13:41.403
- Okay.

13:41.487 --> 13:43.989
Then go to the authorities
before they come to you.

13:44.073 --> 13:45.366
- No.

13:45.449 --> 13:47.201
Not an option.
- Dad.

13:47.284 --> 13:48.369
- No.

13:49.954 --> 13:52.206
Let me call the shots, son.

13:53.457 --> 13:56.168
Right now
we need to be family.

13:56.252 --> 13:59.171
I need to know
that you're in my corner.

14:01.340 --> 14:02.675
- Uh-huh.

14:05.261 --> 14:07.513
I'm in your corner.

14:07.596 --> 14:09.932
- Thanks. Means a lot.

14:10.724 --> 14:14.270
Maybe one day
that'll be a corner office

14:14.353 --> 14:15.980
in Wayne Tower.

14:21.860 --> 14:25.281
[ambient background noise]

14:30.536 --> 14:33.747
[electricity crackling,
buzzing]

14:41.880 --> 14:44.133
- Hey.
- Morning, all.

14:44.216 --> 14:47.011
What's he carrying?
- He has a crate of whiskey.

14:47.094 --> 14:49.847
Several hostages.
And two days' battery charge.

14:49.930 --> 14:51.390
- Whiskey? That's not good.

14:51.473 --> 14:52.808
- I'm sure
you can talk him down.

14:52.891 --> 14:54.852
He always speaks
very highly of you.

14:54.935 --> 14:56.353
- Did he mention
I fucked his wife?

14:56.437 --> 14:58.105
- He does mention that.

14:58.188 --> 15:01.442
But in a philosophical
sort of way.

15:01.525 --> 15:02.526
Mostly.

15:02.610 --> 15:04.486
- So you want me
to go in there

15:04.570 --> 15:05.821
for my regular fee

15:05.904 --> 15:07.615
and extract a sad drunk
with a death ray

15:07.698 --> 15:09.033
who has every reason
to despise me?

15:09.116 --> 15:10.576
- That's classy, Alfred.

15:10.659 --> 15:13.495
Using your sordid love life
to gauge a pay rise.

15:13.579 --> 15:14.580
- If I was married
to a billionaire,

15:14.663 --> 15:15.789
I'd have much more class.

15:15.873 --> 15:18.000
- Ha ha ha!
- Ouch.

15:18.083 --> 15:20.336
- Touché.

15:20.419 --> 15:23.213
Okay, give me a number.
- Double.

15:23.297 --> 15:26.592
- Go get him.
Try to make it quick.

15:26.675 --> 15:28.510
- Any ideas?
- Yes.

15:28.594 --> 15:30.179
His suit has a kill switch.

15:30.262 --> 15:32.348
- I'm not gonna kill him.
- No.

15:33.307 --> 15:35.976
It's a small switch
at the base of the neck plate.

15:36.060 --> 15:37.603
Press it,
and you'll cut his power.

15:37.686 --> 15:40.022
His guns'll go off line,
and he won't be able to move.

15:40.105 --> 15:41.190
But he'll be fine.

15:41.273 --> 15:42.274
- Does he know
about the switch?

15:42.358 --> 15:43.692
- 'Fraid so.

15:43.776 --> 15:45.694
Now, he'll be fine
for about five minutes.

15:45.778 --> 15:48.656
Then we'll need to plug him in
to this baby for a recharge.

15:48.739 --> 15:51.158
- Or else what?
- He'll die.

15:51.241 --> 15:52.534
- Oh, good to know.

15:52.618 --> 15:54.328
I'll get on with it then.
- Thank you.

15:54.411 --> 15:56.497
- I'll fire up the bio-charges.

15:56.580 --> 15:58.957
[helicopter blades
thrum distantly]

16:00.209 --> 16:02.544
- Martha.
[Lucius murmuring to himself]

16:02.628 --> 16:04.505
When Thomas came to see me
yesterday,

16:04.588 --> 16:05.923
he had Samantha with him.

16:06.006 --> 16:07.966
But my mum said
she was working yesterday.

16:08.050 --> 16:09.593
- Why would she say that?

16:09.677 --> 16:12.221
- I think she might be
seeing a man.

16:12.304 --> 16:14.223
I was wondering
if she'd said anything.

16:14.306 --> 16:17.601
- Switch. Behind the neck.
Don't overthink it.

16:17.685 --> 16:20.020
Can't risk
any civilian casualties.

16:20.813 --> 16:24.733
[announcer on TV in background]

16:24.817 --> 16:29.488
[Gully muttering to himself]

16:43.919 --> 16:46.088
- Gully, it's Alfie.
I'm coming in.

16:46.171 --> 16:47.798
- Alfie.

16:47.881 --> 16:49.591
Come on in, son.

16:49.675 --> 16:51.593
Come and have a drink with me.

16:51.677 --> 16:53.262
- All right, Gull?
Been awhile.

16:53.345 --> 16:56.181
- Yeah, someone fetch
my old friend here

16:56.265 --> 16:57.891
a bottle, will you?

17:01.145 --> 17:02.771
[weapon power up hum]

17:02.855 --> 17:05.774
A drink for my friend.

17:05.858 --> 17:09.570
[announcer continues
on TV]

17:12.614 --> 17:14.074
- Thanks, mate.

17:15.242 --> 17:17.286
[power down hum]

17:17.369 --> 17:19.329
- I, uh...

17:19.413 --> 17:22.791
I thought they might call you.
- Oh, yeah? Why's that?

17:22.875 --> 17:25.461
- Someone they thought
that I could trust.

17:25.544 --> 17:29.131
- Hmm.
- Someone who could get close.

17:29.214 --> 17:31.800
You want me to turn around?

17:31.884 --> 17:34.470
Make it easy for you?

17:34.553 --> 17:36.889
- When have you ever made
things easy for me, Gully?

17:36.972 --> 17:38.432
- [chuckles]

17:41.310 --> 17:43.270
- So what's this
all about then?

17:43.353 --> 17:45.481
Why'd you run off?
- [sighs] Ohh...

17:45.564 --> 17:47.691
I'm a wretched bloody serf,
aren't I?

17:47.775 --> 17:49.860
Bound to my master's land

17:49.943 --> 17:52.821
and the whims
of a rotting nobility.

17:52.905 --> 17:54.490
I wanted freedom.

17:54.573 --> 17:56.325
- I don't blame you
for going doolally,

17:56.408 --> 17:57.826
the way you have to live.

17:57.910 --> 18:00.579
But on the bright side,
you're Captain Blighty.

18:00.662 --> 18:02.790
People love you.

18:02.873 --> 18:05.876
- Yeah, that's what they say,
isn't it? Hah.

18:06.835 --> 18:09.421
Not true though.

18:09.505 --> 18:11.965
No, they--they're scared of me.

18:12.049 --> 18:13.842
- Of course they're scared,
the way you carry on.

18:13.926 --> 18:15.135
I mean, look around.

18:15.219 --> 18:16.678
- [chuckles]

18:16.762 --> 18:19.181
- But on the plus side,
there's a lot of love there.

18:19.264 --> 18:20.682
When you're not being a cunt.

18:20.766 --> 18:23.936
- [laughs]

18:24.019 --> 18:25.479
- Cheers.

18:27.815 --> 18:32.236
- You know, this man here,
he fucked my wife.

18:32.319 --> 18:34.321
- Steady on.
Water under the bridge, eh?

18:34.404 --> 18:35.697
- Fucked my wife.

18:35.781 --> 18:39.451
And came this close
to killing me

18:39.535 --> 18:41.995
with a sharpened stick
right here.

18:43.455 --> 18:46.166
You know what?

18:46.250 --> 18:49.711
He's the only friend I've got
in the whole bloody world.

18:49.795 --> 18:51.547
- Who said I'm your friend?

18:51.630 --> 18:54.633
[tense music]

18:54.716 --> 18:56.385
♪ ♪

18:56.468 --> 18:59.179
- You are my friend.

18:59.263 --> 19:00.764
Aren't you, Alfie?

19:03.517 --> 19:05.394
- Of course I am.

19:05.477 --> 19:07.688
- Come any closer...
[power up hum]

19:07.771 --> 19:11.316
I'm gonna have to stick
a very small hole

19:11.400 --> 19:13.318
right through your temple.

19:14.862 --> 19:16.238
- [chuckles]

19:16.321 --> 19:17.698
Fair play.

19:24.621 --> 19:27.583
[soft organ music]

19:27.666 --> 19:34.715
♪ ♪

19:55.944 --> 19:57.988
- Ahh.

19:59.948 --> 20:02.159
Sorry. Where are my manners?

20:05.871 --> 20:07.414
Please yourself.

20:10.542 --> 20:12.211
What about you, miss?

20:12.294 --> 20:13.962
- No, thank you.

20:20.052 --> 20:22.763
- You wouldn't be a Thistle?
- No.

20:22.846 --> 20:24.264
- You point them out to me?

20:29.436 --> 20:30.437
Ah.

20:30.520 --> 20:31.688
Thank you. Noted.

20:31.772 --> 20:34.775
- You don't know the Thistles?

20:34.858 --> 20:35.859
- No.

20:35.943 --> 20:38.278
- So why are you here?

20:40.405 --> 20:43.867
- I'm here for Jessica.
- You knew Jessica?

20:44.826 --> 20:46.370
- I did.

20:47.537 --> 20:51.583
- What a terrible,
horrible tragedy.

20:54.336 --> 20:55.754
- It's horrible.

20:57.714 --> 20:59.841
It's not my fault.

20:59.925 --> 21:01.802
I had no choice.

21:03.512 --> 21:05.180
- I'm sorry?

21:05.263 --> 21:08.266
- No, I'm sorry.
I'm, uh, raving and--

21:10.769 --> 21:13.063
A wee bit under the weather.

21:13.146 --> 21:15.065
- All rise.

21:19.569 --> 21:22.114
- What do you know
about pharmacology?

21:22.197 --> 21:24.324
- A little. Why?

21:24.408 --> 21:26.785
- Do you think a drug could
make someone kill?

21:26.868 --> 21:29.204
For someone who didn't want to?

21:29.288 --> 21:32.124
- Sure. I guess it's possible.

21:32.207 --> 21:34.418
But I've never heard
of anything like that.

21:37.921 --> 21:40.549
What does Thomas say?
- Thomas?

21:40.632 --> 21:42.050
Oh.

21:42.134 --> 21:45.303
You know doctors.
Too much jargon.

21:45.387 --> 21:48.432
Couldn't understand
half of what he said.

21:48.515 --> 21:50.392
- That's doctors for you.

21:50.475 --> 21:53.270
- No offense.
- None taken.

21:57.190 --> 21:59.109
- I have to meet
Sam and Mrs. P.

22:00.360 --> 22:03.905
But, um, you can handle it
from here, right?

22:03.989 --> 22:06.908
- Sure. Alfie'll come through.

22:06.992 --> 22:09.786
Always does.
- I'll check in with you later.

22:12.372 --> 22:15.917
- Lucius, do not get married.

22:16.001 --> 22:18.587
- You ever thought of children,
Alfie?

22:18.670 --> 22:19.921
- Thought of them?
- Mm.

22:20.005 --> 22:21.173
- Yeah.

22:21.256 --> 22:22.758
Not much,
but I have thought of them.

22:22.841 --> 22:25.677
- I always wanted children.

22:25.761 --> 22:27.721
A proper family, you know?

22:27.804 --> 22:29.306
- You're not a domestic animal,
Gully.

22:29.389 --> 22:31.391
- Oh?
- There's no shame in that.

22:31.475 --> 22:35.145
Homes and gardens,
settees and doilies.

22:35.228 --> 22:36.605
Not your purview.

22:36.688 --> 22:39.316
- Well...[laughs]
that's you talking.

22:39.399 --> 22:41.109
- I daresay.

22:41.193 --> 22:45.489
- No. You know,
Melanie didn't love me.

22:45.572 --> 22:48.742
That was the problem.

22:48.825 --> 22:52.412
I couldn't make her love me.

22:52.496 --> 22:55.999
- That was a long time ago, eh?
Best look to the future.

22:56.083 --> 22:58.043
- She loved you though.

22:58.126 --> 23:00.087
- A passing infatuation.

23:01.546 --> 23:03.965
- What was it

23:04.049 --> 23:06.218
that she saw in you

23:06.301 --> 23:08.762
that--that she didn't see
in me?

23:08.845 --> 23:10.222
- Gully,
that was a long time ago.

23:10.305 --> 23:12.057
- Oh, come on.

23:12.140 --> 23:15.102
Come on. Tell me.

23:17.104 --> 23:19.022
- All right.

23:19.106 --> 23:21.983
I didn't get drunk
all the time.

23:22.067 --> 23:23.819
I didn't beat her.

23:23.902 --> 23:27.322
[dark music]

23:27.405 --> 23:29.282
- Oh.

23:29.366 --> 23:30.617
Mm.
[sniffs]

23:30.700 --> 23:31.993
Good to know.

23:32.702 --> 23:34.871
- Is that
what this is all about?

23:34.955 --> 23:36.832
Melanie?
- I miss her.

23:36.915 --> 23:38.041
- Oh.

23:39.709 --> 23:41.795
- In fact,

23:41.878 --> 23:43.213
when I finish this bottle,

23:43.296 --> 23:45.340
I'm gonna watch the two ten
at Catterick.

23:45.423 --> 23:49.636
And then I'm gonna commandeer
myself a big, bloody ship,

23:49.719 --> 23:52.305
go to America, and find her.

23:52.389 --> 23:54.307
[announcer continues on TV]

23:54.391 --> 23:57.018
- You once told me that
a good soldier faces facts.

23:57.102 --> 23:58.687
- Yeah.

23:58.770 --> 24:00.522
- Well, face the facts, Gully.

24:00.605 --> 24:03.275
The government aren't
letting you go to America.

24:03.358 --> 24:06.194
You're a valuable bit of kit.
A national asset.

24:06.278 --> 24:07.696
They'd sink your bloody ship

24:07.779 --> 24:09.406
before they let the Yanks
or anyone else have you.

24:09.489 --> 24:11.908
- I can't carry on like this,
I...

24:13.660 --> 24:15.537
I got to escape somehow.

24:15.620 --> 24:18.456
- Yeah, fair play.
I don't blame ya.

24:19.833 --> 24:21.668
Why don't we go
back to Fox's place?

24:21.751 --> 24:23.211
Give yourself a while
to come up with

24:23.295 --> 24:24.588
a better plan than this lark.
[cheering on TV]

24:24.671 --> 24:27.299
- Yeah.
- Oh, fuck. Banville Lady.

24:27.382 --> 24:28.884
At 50 to 1, I had her!

24:28.967 --> 24:31.052
I'd be fucking minted. Minted.

24:31.136 --> 24:33.847
If not for Captain Assface.
- Oi.

24:33.930 --> 24:36.266
Show some respect.
- What did you call me, sir?

24:36.349 --> 24:38.476
- You're an assface
car battery.

24:38.560 --> 24:39.811
- Bollocks.

24:39.895 --> 24:41.521
- Watch it.

24:41.605 --> 24:43.565
[weapon powering up]
How dare you.

24:43.648 --> 24:45.400
Oh--ooh...

24:45.483 --> 24:46.401
[power down hum]

24:46.484 --> 24:48.111
- Oof.
- Good riddance.

24:49.654 --> 24:51.156
- Had to be done.

24:51.239 --> 24:52.908
- I'm beginning to suspect

24:52.991 --> 24:54.826
that you're not quite
as good a friend

24:54.910 --> 24:57.954
[voice slowing down]
as I thought you w...

24:58.997 --> 25:00.457
- Sorry, Gull.

25:00.540 --> 25:01.917
Come on, then.

25:02.000 --> 25:04.252
- Hang on a sec.
Where you going?

25:04.336 --> 25:06.838
- Fuck's sake, mate.
First you want him out.

25:06.922 --> 25:08.465
Now you want him to stay.
Which is it?

25:08.548 --> 25:11.509
- He cost me a sure thing.
Now he can pay us back.

25:11.593 --> 25:13.595
- How's that?
- Well, that suit

25:13.678 --> 25:15.472
must be worth
some serious dosh.

25:15.555 --> 25:16.973
Leave it, and you can go.

25:17.057 --> 25:18.433
- Oh, give over.

25:18.516 --> 25:21.728
This is Captain bloody Blighty.
National hero.

25:21.811 --> 25:23.271
He's having a bad day.
We all have them.

25:23.355 --> 25:25.649
- Fuck him.
- Shame on you.

25:25.732 --> 25:27.651
Where's your patriotism?

25:27.734 --> 25:30.111
Where's your compassion?
- Right here.

25:30.195 --> 25:32.155
- All right, calm down, lads.

25:33.365 --> 25:35.158
Thank you--augh!

25:36.493 --> 25:37.702
Ah!

25:40.789 --> 25:41.873
[coughing]

25:46.086 --> 25:49.172
[clattering, yelling]

25:50.924 --> 25:54.094
[overlapping yelling]

26:01.851 --> 26:04.771
- Okay. I need a--a--

26:06.314 --> 26:09.442
[shouting, grunting]

26:13.196 --> 26:14.906
- Easy, mate.

26:14.990 --> 26:17.534
No need for that.
- No need? No need?

26:17.617 --> 26:18.952
50 to 1!

26:19.035 --> 26:21.162
- Bloody horses are
a mug's game, aren't they?

26:21.246 --> 26:24.207
One day you're up,
the next you're down.

26:24.291 --> 26:25.959
Premium Bonds is the thing--

26:26.042 --> 26:27.168
[door thuds opens]

26:27.252 --> 26:28.795
- Ah!
[bang]

26:31.631 --> 26:33.008
[wrench clatters]

26:33.091 --> 26:35.844
- Close your mouth. Come on.

26:36.928 --> 26:39.431
[both grunting]

26:39.514 --> 26:42.559
[children chattering,
laughter]

26:43.768 --> 26:45.478
[background chatter]

26:45.562 --> 26:49.190
- Pretty high!
- [giggling] Mrs. P!

26:49.274 --> 26:50.942
- Mrs. P,

26:51.026 --> 26:54.195
did you tell Alfie
you were working yesterday?

26:54.279 --> 26:57.907
- That boy doesn't know
when to let things lie.

26:57.991 --> 27:01.703
Yes, I did.

27:01.786 --> 27:04.372
That's what I told him.
- Okay.

27:04.456 --> 27:06.499
- It was a lie.

27:06.583 --> 27:08.043
- Okay.

27:09.794 --> 27:12.339
- I was seeing a man.

27:12.422 --> 27:13.590
- Wow.

27:13.673 --> 27:14.924
Tell me everything.

27:15.008 --> 27:16.301
No, I mean, if you want to.

27:16.384 --> 27:19.346
Only if you want to.
I won't pry.

27:19.429 --> 27:22.557
Actually, I will pry.
But you can tell me to shut up.

27:22.640 --> 27:25.435
I know how it is
to have a secret life.

27:25.518 --> 27:28.313
Have to have something
for yourself, right?

27:28.396 --> 27:29.689
- Mm-hmm.

27:31.024 --> 27:32.484
I, uh...

27:34.319 --> 27:36.279
There was an advertisement
in the paper.

27:36.363 --> 27:37.906
- The Lonely Hearts?

27:37.989 --> 27:39.324
My God, that's so brave.

27:39.407 --> 27:41.326
- I wish
they wouldn't call it that.

27:41.409 --> 27:43.745
"Lonely Hearts."
It sounds so sad.

27:43.828 --> 27:46.081
- No, it doesn't.

27:46.164 --> 27:47.832
You're taking action.

27:47.916 --> 27:50.835
Taking control
of your own life.

27:50.919 --> 27:53.671
So how was it? Who'd you meet?

27:53.755 --> 27:55.590
- You won't tell anyone,
will you?

27:55.673 --> 27:58.468
- No, Mary, no. Of course not.

27:58.551 --> 28:00.637
- We met at nice tea rooms.

28:00.720 --> 28:03.681
Good cakes. Adequate tea.

28:03.765 --> 28:06.476
The gentleman
seemed amiable enough.

28:06.559 --> 28:09.270
Till, bold as brass,

28:09.354 --> 28:11.106
he said "carpe diem."

28:11.189 --> 28:14.567
- What does that mean?
- Mm, well, you may well ask.

28:14.651 --> 28:18.613
You're too well brought up,
Martha, so you wouldn't know.

28:18.696 --> 28:23.243
It means, "What about
a bit of how's your father?"

28:23.326 --> 28:26.287
- Whose father?
I don't understand.

28:26.371 --> 28:28.665
- He asked me to go
to a hotel with him

28:28.748 --> 28:30.625
[whispering] and have S-E-X.

28:30.708 --> 28:34.462
[both wheezing]

28:34.546 --> 28:37.966
- Okay.
- [laughs]

28:38.049 --> 28:40.051
- Did you?
- Stop it!

28:40.135 --> 28:42.429
Of course, I didn't.

28:42.512 --> 28:44.764
- You didn't? You swear?
Come on.

28:44.848 --> 28:47.350
- No! I swear.

28:50.395 --> 28:52.021
Would never do that.

28:53.731 --> 28:56.401
- Did you want to?
- No.

28:56.484 --> 28:59.154
- Not even a little bit?

28:59.237 --> 29:01.531
- Well...

29:01.614 --> 29:03.199
Maybe a little bit.
- I knew it.

29:03.283 --> 29:05.577
- Out of curiosity.

29:05.660 --> 29:07.495
You know, more than lust.

29:08.788 --> 29:12.083
I've only ever been
with one man.

29:12.167 --> 29:14.252
I always wondered
if it was different

29:14.335 --> 29:15.962
with different men.

29:17.380 --> 29:20.550
- Uh, yes. You bet it is.

29:22.427 --> 29:24.429
- I suspected as much.

29:29.517 --> 29:31.769
- Mary, don't let
one bad date stop you.

29:33.771 --> 29:35.773
You deserve to be happy.

29:36.941 --> 29:39.402
- Mummy, mummy,
I'm going on the slide!

29:39.486 --> 29:41.696
- Things were so much simpler

29:41.779 --> 29:44.199
back when I met Alfie's father.
- Mummy, look!

29:44.282 --> 29:45.909
- How long
were you two married.?

29:45.992 --> 29:47.577
- 28 years.

29:48.786 --> 29:50.205
- What's the secret?

29:50.288 --> 29:52.957
- Hm.
- Look, Mummy!

29:53.041 --> 29:55.001
- Respect.

29:55.084 --> 29:58.379
You're husband and wife,
for better or worse.

29:58.463 --> 30:01.257
Everything else is
just what passes the time.

30:04.469 --> 30:06.513
- I'll go get
her stuff packed up.

30:14.604 --> 30:16.022
- Mrs. Wayne.

30:16.105 --> 30:17.065
- Yes?

30:17.148 --> 30:20.735
- My name is Dr. Robert Glubb.

30:20.818 --> 30:22.362
We need to talk.

30:23.780 --> 30:25.073
- Not here.

30:26.824 --> 30:28.243
There's a pub in the East End

30:28.326 --> 30:29.744
called
the Queen Anne's Revenge.

30:29.827 --> 30:32.580
Meet me there in half an hour.

30:32.664 --> 30:35.416
[edgy music]

30:35.500 --> 30:40.421
♪ ♪

30:48.304 --> 30:50.098
[power up humming]

30:53.434 --> 30:55.395
- Is he okay?

30:55.478 --> 30:57.480
- I need to run a full
diagnostic to be sure,

30:57.564 --> 31:00.275
but yeah, I think we got him
plugged in just in time.

31:01.818 --> 31:03.903
- He wants to go to America.

31:03.987 --> 31:06.656
To find Melanie.
- Oh, wow.

31:06.739 --> 31:09.701
Good.
- Good? How?

31:09.784 --> 31:12.954
He's never going.
Aziz'd never allow it.

31:13.037 --> 31:15.290
And even if he did, I mean,
look at the state of him.

31:15.373 --> 31:17.542
- Can hear you.

31:17.625 --> 31:18.793
- Sorry, Gull.

31:18.876 --> 31:19.836
[power whining]

31:19.919 --> 31:21.879
Didn't mean anything by it.

31:21.963 --> 31:24.340
- Don't be.

31:24.424 --> 31:26.050
It's true. Look at me.

31:26.134 --> 31:27.927
I'm not a man.

31:30.555 --> 31:32.473
I'm a household appliance.

31:32.557 --> 31:36.144
[solemn music]

31:36.227 --> 31:39.188
♪ ♪

31:39.272 --> 31:42.942
[engine running]

31:47.488 --> 31:50.658
[rock music in background]

31:50.742 --> 31:56.289
♪ ♪

32:01.711 --> 32:03.171
- I'm listening.

32:03.254 --> 32:06.341
- Tell Aziz he can have me
and the lullaby drug

32:06.424 --> 32:07.967
for the right price.

32:08.051 --> 32:10.345
- Well, first I need to know
you are who you say you are.

32:10.428 --> 32:12.847
- [scoffs]
I'm Dr. Glubb all right.

32:12.930 --> 32:14.515
- Convince me.

32:15.558 --> 32:18.102
- I used to work
for your father-in-law.

32:18.186 --> 32:19.479
I developed a completely new

32:19.562 --> 32:21.939
and extremely effective
class of drug.

32:22.023 --> 32:23.858
Psycho-kinetics.

32:23.941 --> 32:26.527
Now I want to sell my
expertise on the open market,

32:26.611 --> 32:29.614
Wayne Enterprises and the CIA
are out to kill me, okay?

32:29.697 --> 32:31.199
I'm Dr. Glubb.

32:31.282 --> 32:34.202
[background chatter]

32:34.285 --> 32:37.121
No one else wants to be me.

32:38.790 --> 32:41.834
- You killed that CIA officer?

32:41.918 --> 32:43.711
- I regret that.

32:43.795 --> 32:45.546
It's unavoidable.

32:45.630 --> 32:47.965
I had to get away from him.

32:48.049 --> 32:51.928
- Okay.
Let's assume you're Glubb.

32:52.011 --> 32:53.554
So why are you coming
to us now?

32:53.638 --> 32:56.516
- My original buyer
was murdered to stop the deal.

32:56.599 --> 32:58.976
There's not many other buyers
who can afford me.

32:59.060 --> 33:01.813
- That original buyer would be
Sir Arnulf Thistle?

33:01.896 --> 33:03.189
- Yes.

33:03.272 --> 33:05.233
Are you interested or not?

33:05.316 --> 33:07.902
- What's the right price?

33:07.985 --> 33:09.904
- I need $5 million a year,

33:09.987 --> 33:13.658
a secure laboratory,
and full protection.

33:13.741 --> 33:14.826
- You don't come cheap.

33:14.909 --> 33:16.536
- I'm worth it. Trust me.

33:18.538 --> 33:20.540
- I'll talk
to the Prime Minister.

33:20.623 --> 33:22.667
- I'll be in touch.
- Wait.

33:22.750 --> 33:24.085
Tell me about Patrick Wayne.

33:24.168 --> 33:26.379
What part does he have
in all this?

33:26.462 --> 33:28.631
- We don't have time.
- Talk fast.

33:28.715 --> 33:31.008
- Wayne's not the one
you have to worry about.

33:31.092 --> 33:34.011
[dramatic music]

33:34.095 --> 33:40.560
♪ ♪

33:47.358 --> 33:49.694
- Go, go, go, go.

33:49.777 --> 33:50.987
[door slams]
Go!

34:06.419 --> 34:08.171
[beeping]

34:09.589 --> 34:13.468
- Change of plan.
We gotta clean up.

34:13.551 --> 34:15.803
- [indistinct].

34:15.887 --> 34:19.932
- No, I don't need clear it
with anyone.

34:20.016 --> 34:21.976
This is my op.

34:22.059 --> 34:23.311
Just do it.

34:23.394 --> 34:24.854
- Yes, ma'am.

34:29.942 --> 34:32.737
- "I hold it true
whate'er befall.

34:32.820 --> 34:35.698
"I feel it when I sorrow most.

34:35.782 --> 34:38.826
"'Tis better
to have loved and lost

34:38.910 --> 34:41.329
then never to have loved
at all."

34:41.412 --> 34:44.207
- Thank you, Lady Catherine.

34:47.502 --> 34:49.170
I believe that's
the last of our eulogies--

34:49.253 --> 34:51.923
- Excuse me.
[ahem]

34:52.006 --> 34:54.717
Sorry to interrupt, padre,
but, uh..

34:54.801 --> 34:56.385
do you mind
if I say a quick word?

34:56.469 --> 34:59.972
- It's not really the moment.
- I'll be just a sec.

35:00.056 --> 35:02.850
This won't take a sec.
[crowd muttering]

35:02.934 --> 35:05.561
I didn't really know
these two.

35:05.645 --> 35:10.983
But wherever they are, I'm sure
they're probably better off.

35:11.067 --> 35:15.321
The fucking world being what
it is these fucking days, eh?

35:15.404 --> 35:17.740
I knew their daughter Jessica.

35:17.824 --> 35:19.617
Not very well.
I only met her yesterday.

35:19.700 --> 35:23.204
But we had a good chat.

35:23.287 --> 35:26.249
And I know
that she is not the monster

35:26.332 --> 35:28.376
that everybody's saying
that she is.

35:30.837 --> 35:33.464
She deserved far better
than what she got.

35:34.882 --> 35:37.218
She was going after my mate,
yeah.

35:38.469 --> 35:41.889
So I had no choice.
[people whispering]

35:41.973 --> 35:44.684
I had to shoot her.
[commotion]

35:44.767 --> 35:48.563
I--she didn't suffer. Hey?

35:48.646 --> 35:53.109
It was a good blot.
Dead before she hit the ground.

35:53.192 --> 35:55.111
No way she felt a thing.

35:55.194 --> 35:57.780
So silver linings
and all that, hey?

35:57.864 --> 36:00.575
There are worse ways to go,
believe me.

36:03.202 --> 36:06.873
I'd say being eaten alive
is probably the worse.

36:06.956 --> 36:08.833
- Uh--
- [chuckles]

36:08.916 --> 36:11.711
I was--
I was out on patrol one day.

36:11.794 --> 36:13.546
This is way back east.

36:13.629 --> 36:17.091
And someone said, "Watch out
for the fucking crocodiles."

36:17.174 --> 36:20.011
[laughs] We thought
that was fucking hilarious.

36:20.094 --> 36:21.721
Fucking crocodiles?

36:21.804 --> 36:23.514
And then, what do you know?
It fucking--

36:23.598 --> 36:25.725
- That's enough.
You need to leave.

36:25.808 --> 36:27.977
- I'm telling a fucking story
here, pal.

36:28.060 --> 36:29.270
- Let's go.

36:29.353 --> 36:31.439
- I'm not fucking finished,
am I?

36:31.522 --> 36:33.357
Hey!
- Vicar!

36:33.441 --> 36:34.942
- Hey!
all: [gasp]

36:35.026 --> 36:36.569
- You need to leave now.

36:36.652 --> 36:40.615
- I'll fucking leave when
I'm ready to fucking leave!

36:40.698 --> 36:42.617
You--fuck!

36:51.459 --> 36:52.877
- Martha?

36:56.213 --> 36:57.673
Samantha?

36:57.757 --> 36:59.175
Anyone home?

37:03.554 --> 37:05.598
- Just us, I'm afraid.

37:08.100 --> 37:10.519
Mind pouring
one of those for me?

37:10.603 --> 37:12.897
And don't be shy.

37:14.607 --> 37:15.900
- Sure.

37:23.032 --> 37:26.202
Uh, where's my father?

37:26.285 --> 37:28.245
- No idea.

37:28.329 --> 37:29.538
When I left this morning,

37:29.622 --> 37:32.124
he seemed very worried
about something.

37:34.919 --> 37:36.087
- Did he?

37:37.380 --> 37:40.925
- You wouldn't happen to know
what he was worried about?

37:41.008 --> 37:42.176
- Nope.

37:43.970 --> 37:46.764
- You're a bad liar.

37:46.847 --> 37:48.975
Especially for a Wayne.

37:50.476 --> 37:52.687
- Uh, well, I assure you,

37:52.770 --> 37:55.773
I'm--I'm not lying.

37:55.856 --> 37:57.692
- Mm-hmm.

37:57.775 --> 37:59.443
How are you and Martha?

38:01.028 --> 38:02.571
- Excuse me?

38:02.655 --> 38:06.367
- Your father and I staying
here is a nuisance, I know.

38:06.450 --> 38:10.538
I'd hate to think I was
the cause of a marital rift.

38:10.621 --> 38:13.791
- No, uh, no rift.

38:13.874 --> 38:15.835
We're, uh, we're great.

38:15.918 --> 38:17.670
Better than ever.

38:17.753 --> 38:18.963
- Hmm.

38:19.046 --> 38:20.798
I'm so glad to hear it.

38:21.799 --> 38:23.009
- Hmm.

38:23.092 --> 38:25.428
[tense music]

38:25.511 --> 38:26.971
♪ ♪

38:27.054 --> 38:29.598
Well, uh, Martha and Samantha
will be home soon.

38:29.682 --> 38:30.891
So I should, um--

38:30.975 --> 38:34.437
I should make
a start on dinner.

38:34.520 --> 38:36.605
- Doesn't your housekeeper
do that?

38:36.689 --> 38:39.567
- Oh, it's her night off.

38:39.650 --> 38:41.652
- Are you good?

38:41.736 --> 38:44.155
In the kitchen?

38:44.238 --> 38:47.199
- Uh, I try.

38:50.161 --> 38:52.038
- Need a hand?

38:53.998 --> 38:56.333
- [swallows] Mm-mm.

38:56.417 --> 38:58.294
No. I'm good.

39:09.388 --> 39:10.765
[thud]

39:12.349 --> 39:14.310
- Hmm.

39:20.066 --> 39:22.026
- Oh, my God.

39:22.109 --> 39:23.611
- Quiet.

39:23.694 --> 39:26.614
- I can't let you do this.
- We don't have time for this.

39:26.697 --> 39:28.949
- I'm serious. No more.
This is going too far. I--

39:29.033 --> 39:30.785
- Patrick, go to your room.

39:30.868 --> 39:34.789
- You can't do this. I'm the--
- Go to your room.

39:49.512 --> 39:53.766
- That was the best funeral
I have ever been to.

39:53.849 --> 39:55.267
- Ah.

39:55.351 --> 39:56.811
You oughta see me at weddings.

39:56.894 --> 39:58.104
- You just ripped away

39:58.187 --> 40:01.065
the whole silly bourgeois
façade of it all.

40:01.148 --> 40:04.193
- Well,
I'll pay for any damages.

40:04.276 --> 40:06.737
- You were fabulous.

40:06.821 --> 40:08.364
Do you need to go
to hospital?

40:08.447 --> 40:12.993
- Hey, no. Soft gits.
Couldn't hurt a fly.

40:13.077 --> 40:14.578
I've had worse, believe me.

40:14.662 --> 40:16.831
- Oh, I do.

40:18.249 --> 40:21.377
Sally Prufrock. Pleasure.

40:21.460 --> 40:23.420
- Wallace MacDougal.

40:23.504 --> 40:26.757
My friends call me Daveboy.
- Why?

40:26.841 --> 40:30.594
- Why?
- Why do they call you Daveboy?

40:30.678 --> 40:32.221
- I've never asked.

40:32.304 --> 40:34.557
- [chuckles]

40:34.640 --> 40:38.811
Oh, you're very funny,
Mr. Daveboy.

40:38.894 --> 40:41.021
Would you like to go
for a drink with me?

40:49.822 --> 40:51.448
- Can I ask you a question?

40:51.532 --> 40:53.242
- Of course.

40:53.325 --> 40:55.578
- When I said that Gully
wanted to go to America

40:55.661 --> 40:57.079
to find Melanie,

40:57.163 --> 40:59.957
you said you thought
that was good. Why?

41:00.040 --> 41:03.460
- It's a reason to live,
however hopeless.

41:03.544 --> 41:04.920
- A reason to live?

41:05.004 --> 41:06.422
It's a bit melodramatic,
don't you think?

41:06.505 --> 41:08.215
- You saw him today.

41:08.299 --> 41:10.634
What do you think?

41:10.718 --> 41:13.554
- I think that Gully Troy's
too much of an arrogant prick

41:13.637 --> 41:15.973
to go quietly.

41:16.056 --> 41:18.017
Always has been.

41:18.100 --> 41:20.436
That's what made him
such a good officer.

41:21.896 --> 41:24.398
- Strange.
- What's that?

41:24.481 --> 41:26.567
- I wouldn't have thought
to classify arrogance

41:26.650 --> 41:30.738
as a characteristic
of good military leadership.

41:30.821 --> 41:32.406
- Trust me.

41:32.489 --> 41:34.617
It's the only fucking
characteristic.

41:38.287 --> 41:42.041
You have to believe
that you're somehow special.

41:42.124 --> 41:45.085
That the rules of life
and death don't apply to you.

41:47.004 --> 41:50.216
That was Gully fucking Troy.

41:51.759 --> 41:54.136
And if you served under him,
that was you too.

41:55.387 --> 41:58.599
- I'm not sure how much
of that Gully's left.

41:58.682 --> 42:00.684
- Mm, people don't change.

42:02.686 --> 42:05.522
- Maybe that's the problem.

42:05.606 --> 42:08.317
He didn't change
when he had the chance.

42:08.400 --> 42:11.487
Now it's too late,
and he knows that.

42:17.326 --> 42:18.869
- Blimey.

42:18.953 --> 42:21.747
You're a real ray of
fucking sunshine.

42:21.830 --> 42:23.207
- Sorry.

42:23.290 --> 42:25.960
Polite conversation's
never been my strong suit.

42:26.043 --> 42:27.169
- Mm.

42:39.640 --> 42:42.643
I should go back,
check on Gully.

42:45.854 --> 42:47.481
Thanks for the beer, Alfie.

42:49.483 --> 42:52.403
[soft music]

42:52.486 --> 42:59.535
♪ ♪

43:00.911 --> 43:04.081
[Mott the Hoople's "All
the Way From Memphis" playing]

43:04.164 --> 43:08.961
♪ ♪

43:09.044 --> 43:10.045
- Yeah?

43:10.129 --> 43:12.006
- Sandra here?

43:12.089 --> 43:14.091
- She's not taking visitors.

43:15.551 --> 43:22.641
♪ ♪

43:23.684 --> 43:25.769
- Bloody parasites.

43:27.104 --> 43:30.482
- ♪ Forgot
my six-string razor ♪

43:30.566 --> 43:31.692
[record scratches]

43:31.775 --> 43:33.527
- Party's over. Everyone out.

43:33.610 --> 43:34.695
- Who the hell are you?

43:34.778 --> 43:36.196
- I'm the man giving you
a choice.

43:36.280 --> 43:37.865
Out a door,
out a fucking window.

43:37.948 --> 43:39.158
Makes no difference to me.

43:39.241 --> 43:40.868
- Hey, there's no reason
to be so--

43:40.951 --> 43:41.952
- Shut it!

43:42.911 --> 43:45.205
Oh, there's a privet hedge.
You'll be all right.

43:45.289 --> 43:47.916
Out!
[guests muttering]

43:49.501 --> 43:51.545
And you lot, out!

43:51.628 --> 43:54.131
[low chatter]

44:15.110 --> 44:16.528
[whispers] Hey.

44:19.198 --> 44:20.616
- Alfie?

44:23.035 --> 44:24.411
What are you doing here?

44:24.495 --> 44:27.790
- I was in the area.
Got peckish.

44:27.873 --> 44:31.251
Thought I'd see
if you could do us a sandwich.

44:31.335 --> 44:33.420
[soft music]

44:33.504 --> 44:35.297
- No.

44:35.381 --> 44:36.965
No sandwiches.

44:39.051 --> 44:40.594
- Never mind.

44:40.677 --> 44:42.679
I expect there's biscuits
at least.

44:46.392 --> 44:48.602
Are you all right?

44:48.685 --> 44:50.437
- No, I'm not.

44:58.904 --> 45:01.365
Are you really here
for a sandwich?

45:05.285 --> 45:06.537
- No.

45:07.955 --> 45:09.164
- Yes.

45:11.041 --> 45:14.002
Tell him to call me
as soon as he lands.

45:14.086 --> 45:15.963
Thanks.

45:16.046 --> 45:17.631
- Samantha's all tucked in.

45:17.714 --> 45:19.425
She's fast asleep already.

45:19.508 --> 45:20.843
- Thank you.

45:22.302 --> 45:23.971
Do you know where Thomas is?

45:24.054 --> 45:25.472
[door opens]

45:27.808 --> 45:30.602
- Good even, Thomas.
- Oh, hey, Mrs. P.

45:31.979 --> 45:33.647
- Where have you been?

45:33.730 --> 45:35.649
- Well, my father and Virginia
are out for the night,

45:35.732 --> 45:38.110
and so I thought
I'd pick up dinner for two.

45:38.193 --> 45:40.320
I got the Sole
with the lemon butter

45:40.404 --> 45:42.281
from Mirabelle's
that you like.

45:44.616 --> 45:46.994
- Really?
- Yeah.

45:47.077 --> 45:49.997
I'll heat it up
and open the wine now.

45:50.080 --> 45:51.498
- Okay.

45:54.084 --> 45:55.752
What?

45:55.836 --> 45:57.546
- Have a lovely evening.

46:03.510 --> 46:04.887
- Thanks.

46:15.731 --> 46:17.357
This is really--
- So, I was--

46:17.441 --> 46:18.734
[both chuckle]

46:18.817 --> 46:22.070
Um, after you.
- No, after you.

46:24.448 --> 46:28.368
- Well, I was--I was just
thinking that, um...

46:28.452 --> 46:30.579
we need to take a step back
from all this drama

46:30.662 --> 46:34.833
and remember
the important stuff.

46:34.917 --> 46:36.877
- That's funny.

46:36.960 --> 46:38.962
I was thinking
the exact same thing.

46:40.464 --> 46:45.010
- Which is
that we love each other.

46:45.093 --> 46:46.553
And we have
a beautiful daughter.

46:46.637 --> 46:48.972
- And nothing else matters.
- Exactly.

46:51.433 --> 46:52.809
- I'm sorry I lied to you.

46:53.894 --> 46:55.354
I'll never do that again.

46:57.689 --> 46:59.483
- Yeah, well.

46:59.566 --> 47:02.945
I'm sorry that I was

47:03.028 --> 47:08.575
judgmental and self-righteous.

47:08.659 --> 47:10.953
[phone rings]

47:11.036 --> 47:14.039
I'll go.
[phone ringing]

47:19.711 --> 47:21.588
Wayne Residence.
Thomas speaking.

47:21.672 --> 47:27.010
- ♪ I hear you whispering ♪

47:27.094 --> 47:33.350
♪ But nobody is there ♪

47:33.433 --> 47:39.189
♪ My eyes are still
lingering ♪

47:39.273 --> 47:45.070
♪ On your empty chair ♪

47:45.153 --> 47:46.363
♪ My darling...♪

47:46.446 --> 47:47.823
- Is everything okay?

47:47.906 --> 47:53.161
[song continues in background]

47:53.245 --> 47:55.914
Thomas?

47:55.998 --> 47:57.249
What's wrong?

48:07.884 --> 48:09.177
- Nothing.

48:09.261 --> 48:11.096
- Obviously something is.

48:11.179 --> 48:12.973
Who was that on the phone?

48:15.142 --> 48:16.727
- I can't tell you.

48:17.894 --> 48:19.980
- Why not?
- I don't trust you.

48:20.063 --> 48:21.815
- Come on.

48:21.898 --> 48:24.359
I thought we just now agreed
to get past all this.

48:24.443 --> 48:26.778
- Easy for you to say.

48:26.862 --> 48:28.905
- What's that supposed to mean?

48:33.910 --> 48:35.078
- Look at us.

48:36.913 --> 48:39.249
We're both prisoners.

48:39.333 --> 48:40.584
We're both of us guilty.

48:40.667 --> 48:44.129
- Thomas?
There's no need to exaggerate.

48:44.212 --> 48:47.841
- [breathing hard]

48:49.384 --> 48:53.055
- [gasps]
- [grunts]

48:53.138 --> 48:56.099
- What are you doing?
- I'm sorry. No choice.

48:56.183 --> 48:59.102
[both grunting]

48:59.186 --> 49:02.105
[intense music]

49:02.189 --> 49:09.154
♪ ♪

49:25.462 --> 49:26.922
- [gasps]

49:29.508 --> 49:32.886
[gasps] Thomas!

49:32.969 --> 49:34.638
Thomas.

49:34.721 --> 49:38.350
[silently] Please, Thomas.
Please don't do this. Please.

49:39.518 --> 49:41.061
- I'll see you in hell.

49:41.144 --> 49:42.646
[thud]

49:43.772 --> 49:45.232
- Oh, my God.

49:45.315 --> 49:48.318
Hang on, Martha. Hang on!

49:50.487 --> 49:52.572
- ♪ I gave you-- ♪

49:56.868 --> 49:59.079
[line ringing]

49:59.162 --> 50:02.499
- Yes, I need an ambulance now
at 34 Edith Row.

50:02.582 --> 50:06.253
[panting]
And send the police as well.

50:09.881 --> 50:12.843
[adventurous music]

50:12.926 --> 50:20.016
♪ ♪
